WEBVTT

00:02.896 --> 00:05.246
I wish I had better news
for you, Donovan.

00:05.289 --> 00:07.683
That dockworker's testimony...

00:07.726 --> 00:10.381
I'm not sure we can get past it.

00:12.514 --> 00:13.950
How long's it been, Keith?

00:13.994 --> 00:16.518
30 years?

00:16.561 --> 00:19.260
And Donovan's never been
convicted with you at his side.

00:19.303 --> 00:21.479
We thank you for that.

00:21.523 --> 00:22.872
But...

00:22.916 --> 00:24.918
now you got to be
honest with us.

00:24.961 --> 00:27.659
What should we be preparing for?

00:27.703 --> 00:29.661
Barring a miracle,

00:29.705 --> 00:31.707
a "guilty" sentence.

00:31.750 --> 00:34.536
And with Judge Stanley,

00:34.579 --> 00:37.844
a former D.A.,
his history on sentencing

00:37.887 --> 00:40.977
for this type of thing and...
Donovan's record...

00:42.587 --> 00:45.025
we are almost certainly
looking at the maximum.

00:45.068 --> 00:47.201
The full 25 years.

00:47.244 --> 00:50.030
My God...

00:50.073 --> 00:52.684
That's the rest of your life.

00:52.728 --> 00:56.210
He did say "barring a miracle."

00:56.253 --> 00:59.778
I guess I'll just
have to pray for that, huh?

00:59.822 --> 01:02.390
You'll pray, too.

01:02.433 --> 01:04.305
Won't you, son?

01:06.000 --> 01:12.074
